      "ts": "2026-05-06T19:09:22.556Z",
      "text": "Responder ao usuário em português conforme preferência global registrada."
    },
    {
      "id": "decision-2026-05-07-f58c86",
      "ts": "2026-05-07T20:33:22.024Z",
      "text": "Refresh init and side-panel scaffolds as docs/context-only slice after offline /init reported no file writes."
    },
    {
      "id": "decision-2026-05-07-0c3cbf",
      "ts": "2026-05-07T20:47:14.009Z",
      "text": "Do not promote lib-bins as a mandatory gate yet; local serial measurement hit the 600s Jcode supervision timeout while tests were still passing."
    },
    {
      "id": "decision-2026-05-07-5b0347",
      "ts": "2026-05-07T20:51:37.321Z",
      "text": "Issue #1 first slice (`jcode-harness safe-eval`) is already present in current source and e2e coverage; validated locally and aligned selfdev jcode-harness binary before moving to next issue."
    },
    {
      "id": "decision-2026-05-07-3d8a2f",
      "ts": "2026-05-07T21:07:46.124Z",
      "text": "For issue #2, implement a deterministic manifest-only `jcode-harness demo` first, rather than auto-running demos, so README/product claims are reproducible without triggering project writes, providers, network, MCP, browser, or credentials by default."
    },
    {
      "id": "decision-2026-05-07-8ad931",
      "ts": "2026-05-07T21:15:35.766Z",
      "text": "For `demo run`, block manifest entries with `project_writes=true` by default and only run them with explicit `--allow-writes`, so issue #2 demos stay reproducible without accidental workspace mutation."
    },
    {
      "id": "decision-2026-05-07-b71c29",
      "ts": "2026-05-07T21:21:56.855Z",
      "text": "Use `--sandbox` as the preferred way to execute project-writing demos: it permits reproducible evidence while keeping the requested repository clean and deleting the temporary workspace by default."
    },
    {
      "id": "decision-2026-05-07-b132df",
      "ts": "2026-05-07T21:37:19.701Z",
      "text": "Expose `jcode-harness session list --json` as the first issue #4 headless runtime slice: read-only/offline session metadata now, while mutable spawn/attach/resume APIs remain follow-up work."
    },
    {
      "id": "decision-2026-05-07-10dee0",
      "ts": "2026-05-07T21:46:41.371Z",
      "text": "Expose `jcode-harness session show <id> --json` as a local-session-only, read-only headless metadata API with transcript preview opt-in via bounded `--preview N`, keeping external imported session show semantics for later source-specific slices."
    },
    {
      "id": "decision-2026-05-08-d2bfe3",
      "ts": "2026-05-08T11:25:03.238Z",
      "text": "Completed issue #13 safety slice add working_dir metadata to AgentInfo, swarm list formatting, and cleanup dry-run labels without changing live cleanup behavior."
    },
    {
      "id": "decision-2026-05-08-5a16d0",
      "ts": "2026-05-08T11:43:01.247Z",
      "text": "Completed issue #13 observability slice: structured swarm events now carry member run_id, role, status, and working_dir metadata when recorded for known members, and debug recent/since/subscribe expose those fields additively."
    },
    {
      "id": "decision-2026-05-08-134767",
      "ts": "2026-05-08T11:53:09.078Z",
      "text": "Completed issue #13 UX slice: default swarm list output now summarizes run groups, including mixed run IDs and unscoped legacy members, with a scoped-list hint while preserving scoped run output behavior."
    },
    {
      "id": "decision-2026-05-08-1b295d",
      "ts": "2026-05-08T12:02:53.529Z",
      "text": "Completed issue #13 idempotency slice: explicit operation_id now deduplicates swarm message/dm/channel fanout by replaying prior Done/Error through swarm mutation state without changing default messages."
    },
    {
      "id": "decision-2026-05-08-651880",
      "ts": "2026-05-08T12:13:13.823Z",
      "text": "Completed issue #13 stop idempotency slice: stop now replays persisted final responses before target lookup and begins mutation before emitting close/removal side effects, preventing duplicate close requests on retry."
    },
    {
      "id": "decision-2026-05-08-da8746",
      "ts": "2026-05-08T12:20:07.164Z",
      "text": "Completed issue #13 resolved stop identity slice: live stop mutations now use resolved target session IDs, preserving exact-ID replay while preventing reused aliases from replaying stale stop results."
    },
    {
      "id": "decision-2026-05-08-6c4197",
      "ts": "2026-05-08T13:05:48.284Z",
      "text": "Completed issue #13 spawn idempotency follow-up: explicit operation_id/request_nonce spawn keys now ignore generated run_id drift, preserving default non-operation-id spawn key specificity."
    },
    {
      "id": "decision-2026-05-08-09d952",
      "ts": "2026-05-08T13:13:45.058Z",
      "text": "Completed issue #13 await scoping guard: implicit await_members now infers a sole active owned run_id or errors with an explicit-scope hint when multiple active owned runs are present, while preserving explicit scopes and no-run fallback."
    },
    {
      "id": "decision-2026-05-08-0faa68",
      "ts": "2026-05-08T13:26:46.046Z",
      "text": "Completed issue #13 assign_next idempotency slice: explicit operation_id/request_nonce now replays the original assign_next assignment instead of advancing to another task, while default assign_next remains non-idempotent."
    },
    {
      "id": "decision-2026-05-08-f5b780",
      "ts": "2026-05-08T13:36:33.662Z",
      "text": "Completed issue #13 task_control idempotency slice: explicit operation_id/request_nonce now replays wake/start/resume task_control responses without repeating side effects, while default task_control remains non-idempotent."
    },
    {
      "id": "decision-2026-05-08-0335ee",
      "ts": "2026-05-08T13:51:59.046Z",
      "text": "Completed issue #13 assign_task idempotency slice: explicit operation_id/request_nonce now replays the original assign_task assignment across payload drift, while default assign_task remains payload-derived."
    },
    {
      "id": "decision-2026-05-08-5f1d21",
      "ts": "2026-05-08T13:59:51.791Z",
      "text": "Completed issue #13 fill_slots idempotency slice: explicit operation_id now derives a stable run scope and per-slot assign_next nonces, so retries replay original slot assignments instead of filling additional tasks."
    },
    {
      "id": "decision-2026-05-08-f7c593",
      "ts": "2026-05-08T14:06:58.312Z",
      "text": "Completed issue #13 coordinator retry slice: coordinator-only swarm tool actions now self-promote and retry once for assignment/control operations when the server returns a coordinator-denial error."
    },
    {
      "id": "decision-2026-05-08-9cfee9",
      "ts": "2026-05-08T14:13:10.908Z",
      "text": "Completed issue #13 run_plan operation_id slice: explicit operation_id now provides a stable run scope and versioned per-slot assign_next nonces so same-phase retries replay while later plan versions can continue assigning newly ready tasks."
    }
